<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="90" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1865,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1901,1927]" pageId="7" pageNumber="90">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head valve with 9 low, wide radial ribs. Tegmentum evenly sculptured with flattened granules in quincuncial pattern, each granule with 9 pores of aesthetes. Pores of megalaesthetes 
<quantity box="[1114,1174,1938,1964]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 µm</quantity>
in diameter. Tail valve mucro anterior. Dorsal scales with 11–13 longitudinal ribs in distal half. Five gills per side. Major radular lateral teeth with unidentate sickle-shaped cusps.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
