</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,588,1939,1963]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[531,588,1939,1963]" pageId="8" pageNumber="91" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Philippines, Balicasag Island, PANGLAO 2004, stn L61-64, 9°30.9’N 123°40.8’E, 87–111 m, paratype (MNHN-IM-2013-67045) BL 3.5 mm: A. Radula; B. Centeral and first lateral teeth of radula.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,150,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">Description.</emphasis>
Chiton of small size, BL up to 4.0 mm, moderately raised (dorsal elevation 
<quantity box="[1190,1267,151,177]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1684" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" unit="in" value="0.46">0.46 in</quantity>
valve V), back evenly rounded, valves not beaked, color of tegmentum white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">Head valve semicircular with nine low, wide radial ribs; posterior margin widely V-shaped, notched in the middle, noticeably larger than tail valve. Intermediate valves approximately of same length, rather narrow, trapezoidal with narrow, strongly raised lateral areas, anterior margin convex in valve II, almost straight in valves III–VII, curved inwardly towards the rounded sides, hind margin straight, with broken, somewhat swollen apices, lateral areas separated from the central area by diagonal depressions. Tail valve half elliptical, anterior margin straight with slightly protruding sides, mucro anterior, not projecting, anterior slope convex, posterior slope concave.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">
Tegmentum evenly sculptured with flattened granules in quincuncial pattern, each granule with 9 pores of aesthetes. Pores of megalaesthetes rounded, 
<quantity box="[612,671,475,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 µm</quantity>
in diameter, most other pores slit-like, 
<quantity box="[1111,1198,474,501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 µm</quantity>
in width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">Articulamentum thin, apophyses short, trapezoidal, connected behind anterior tegmental margin, slit formula 10/1/8.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">
Girdle of moderate width, 
<quantity box="[499,586,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long in 
<typeStatus box="[680,778,583,609]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">holotype</typeStatus>
(BL 4.0 mm), covered with wide, bent, imbricating scales 50 x 
<quantity box="[206,281,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="70.0">70 µm</quantity>
, sculptured with 11–13 longitudinal ribs in distal half, top of scales rounded, some of these longitudinal ribs tend to form spherule on top of scale. Marginal spicules of two kinds: rare long, smooth needles on short bristle 100 x 8 μm and numerous flattened, sharply pointed spicules 60 x 20 μm with 5 longitudinal ribs on dorsal side. Two rows of ventral scales near margin 45 x 16 μm with 3–4 short ribs in upper half, other ventral scales rectangular, flat, smooth 40 x 15 μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" box="[199,998,798,825]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">
<typeStatus box="[199,303,799,825]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">Holotype</typeStatus>
has 5 gills arranged from valve VI to valve VIII on each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">
Radula of the 
<typeStatus box="[360,458,835,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[466,553,835,861]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
long with 56 transverse rows of mature teeth. Central tooth slender, elongate, with a small rhomboid blade, longitudinal rib and slightly broadened base. First lateral tooth larger. Major lateral tooth with unicuspid and sickle-shaped head, dorsal part of the head with 2 shallow grooves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,943,969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[379,475,943,969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2021" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2021" box="[520,792,943,969]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Connexochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="costatus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[520,792,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="92">Connexochiton costatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[803,866,943,969]" pageId="9" pageNumber="92" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(MNHN-IM-2013-49560) has slit formula 7/1/7. The new species differs from its congeners by having 9 radial ribs on the head valve and flattened granules of the tegmentum (vs. no ribs on head valve and convex granules in all other species of the genus).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
